  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.3916" xml:lang="fr">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>

        <p>Monsieur, Je vous remercie très sincèrement des deux lettres que vous avez voulu m’adresser, ainsi comme de l’envoi de <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.subjects#S.3344">
            <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">l’American Journal of Philology</hi>
          </ref> et je vous prie d’en remercier aussi M. le Dr. <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.5347">
Gildersleeve</persName>
          <note n="1" place="foot" type="editorial">Cf. footnote 1 (<ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.letter.3861">Briefnummer 1484</ref>).</note>. Il est vrai, je possédais déjà l’étude de M. <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1714">Harrison</persName>
          <note n="2" place="foot" type="editorial">Cf. footnote 1 (<ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.letter.3860">Briefnummer 1483</ref>). Cable had procured the article for Schuchardt, considering it a better source of data than his own novels.</note> laquelle du reste repose entièrement sur les matériaux publiés par votre compatriote M. le Dr. <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2167">Mercier</persName>
          <note n="3" place="foot" type="editorial">Dr. <persName
              ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2167">Alfred Mercier</persName> (1816-1894), a native Louisianan physician and writer. He was concerned with the promotion of <ref
              target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.226">
French</ref> and <ref
              target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.subjects#S.839">
Creole language</ref> and culture in <placeName
              ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.places#PL.5884">Louisiana</placeName>. For that purpose he co-founded <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.subjects#S.3465">
L’Athénée Louisianais</ref> in 1875. His later literary and philologist works implement and discuss the creole language of Louisiana (Jumonville 2002).</note>. Je lirai prochainement vos romans créoles; ma seule excuse de ne les connaître pas encore consiste à lire très peu de romans</p>
        <closer>
          <salute>Veuillez agréer, Monsieur, l’assurance de ma parfaite considération</salute>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.109">H. Schuchardt</persName>
          </signed>
        </closer>
      </div>
